metadata.name: Microreactors/A Box of Chocolates #5
metadata.description:
Objects drifting in a cell generate beautiful and complex patterns. They look like "Concentration fluctuations caused by thermal convection in microreactors". It also evokes Forrest Gump's famous line "Life is like a box of chocolates".

There is a phase difference between adjacent cells, generating similar but different patterns.

Each of them can be seen as a parallel world of life.

In addition, the observer can interfere with the pattern by clicking and dragging the mouse.

metadata.name: Triangle Subdivisions #239
metadata.description:
A study on geometric triangle subdivisions resulted in this artwork.
Only 638 bytes of JavaScript are needed to create a variety of different subdivisions (and no libraries are used). 

One tile will be generated for every byte of code.  

An article about this technique can be seen here:
https://josvromans.com/blog/2021/1/triangle-subdivisions/

metadata.name: Intrusive Thoughts (on a loop) #26
metadata.description:
The concept for Intrusive Thoughts was born in the second half of 2022 during a series of therapy sessions.  Genuary 2023 played an important role on getting rid of most of my annoying intrusive thoughts.  Intrusive Thoughts (on a loop) is the first of four releases on the same topic.

Some browsers will need to tap or click to activate sound.  Use arrow up and arrow down to zoom or click on top and bottom.

metadata.name: Lust I #15
metadata.description:
LUST is about the pure joy of creating. Through play, imagination and simplicity. Lust is a minimalistic generative art project divided in three releases (I,II,III). 

The project is based on the algorithm Gravity, used in my previous releases.

metadata.name: Life #2
metadata.description: Life is Lust animated. Since I wrote the algorithm Gravity in 2020 I have been aiming for bringing it to life and animate it in realtime. This is the result in its simplest form.
tags: minimalistic magnetic gravity field animated jmy jimmy herdberg

metadata.name: cliques #219
metadata.description:
clique is defined as:

- /klēk,klik/ (n.) a small group of people, with shared interests or other features in common, who spend time together and do not readily allow others to join them.

cliques can offer safety. (something about numbers.)

cliques can offer a place to be. (for better or worse.)

sometimes cliques have sub-cliques. (the intersections can get a bit complicated.)

sometimes a member of a clique may still feel outside of it. (power dynamics can ruin things.)

occasionally clique dynamics are balanced and the connections between the members pull towards the center. (we can consider that non-toxic.)

often, though, the connections are pulled in various directions and the connection between two members are swayed (or pulled towards) other members. (we can consider that toxic.)

[4 color palettes: monochrome, neon, vibrant rebellion, glacier]

metadata.name: Antigravity #418
metadata.description:
To change size or quality, open the IPFS link in a separate window and append to its url a string like `&quality=400&tiles=9,16`. You may notice two parameters in it: `quality` and `tiles`.

`quality` is an integer from 1 to ~1000, the better the quality — the slower the rendering. Default is 200.

`tiles` is a number of 256×256 px tiles to render. Can be an integer (for square images) or two integers separated with a comma (for rectangular). `tiles=9,16` will make an image with width of 9×256 px = 2304 px and height of 16×256 px = 4096 px. If not set, adapts to screen size.

Press `s` to save the image.
